anging cultural and economic factors and consider what this may signify for the future of a large, secure, and dynamic middle class.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBankruptcyxUnited States. 0aBankruptcyzUnited States. 0aConsumer creditxUnited States. 0aConsumer creditzUnited States. 0aCrédit à la consommationxÉtats-Unis. 0aFaillitexÉtats-Unis. 0aFinance, PersonalxUnited States. 0aFinance, PersonalzUnited States. 0aFinances personnellesxÉtats-UnisxUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aWarren, Elizabeth, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWestbrook, Jay Lawrence, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030012814740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300128147423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300128147/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles